The paper discusses relaying in wireless communications, specifically in cooperative BS systems with microwave link backhauling. This falls under the categories of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), communication (cs.COMM), and multiagent systems (cs.MA). The focus on analyzing the performance of the system using analytical methods based on free probability also suggests a strong likelihood of cs.IT and cs.SI.
